@startuml DigitalWellbeingSystem_ClassDiagram

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 40
skinparam ranksep 35
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor White
    BorderColor #333333
    FontSize 11
}

title <size:20>Digital Wellbeing System</size>\n<size:13>Trace one user action: "User opens Instagram, uses it 30 min, closes it." Follow Step 1 to 7.</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: ENTRY POINT — Facade
' ====================================================================
package "Entry Point" as FM #E8EAF6 {

    class DigitalWellbeingSystem <<Facade>> {
        - tracker : ScreenTimeTracker
        - statsService : UsageStatisticsService
        - retentionMgr : DataRetentionManager
        - repository : UsageRepository
        --
        + initialize() : void
        + onAppOpened(pkg) : void
        + onAppClosed(pkg) : void
        + getUsageStats() : UsageReport
        + getTodayScreenTime() : long
        + getDailyUsage(app) : DailyUsageSummary
        + setDailyLimit(app, min) : void
        + shutdown() : void
    }
}

note top of FM #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "User opens Instagram. The OS calls
    our system. The client only talks to
    this **Facade** class. It delegates
    onAppOpened('com.instagram') down
    to the tracker."
    **Pattern: Facade** | **(SRP, DIP)**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: TRACKER — Singleton
' ====================================================================
package "Tracking" as TM #E3F2FD {

    class ScreenTimeTracker <<Singleton>> {
        - {static} instance : ScreenTimeTracker
        - activeSessions : Map
        - observers : List
        - repository : UsageRepository
        --
        - ScreenTimeTracker(repository)
        + {static} getInstance() : ScreenTimeTracker
        + onAppOpened(app) : void
        + onAppClosed(app) : void
        + getActiveSession(app) : UsageSession
        - notifyObservers(event) : void
    }

    class UsageEvent {
        - app : AppInfo
        - eventType : EventType
        - timestamp : long
        - session : UsageSession
    }

    enum EventType {
        APP_OPENED
        APP_CLOSED
        DAILY_LIMIT_REACHED
    }

    ScreenTimeTracker -down-> UsageEvent : fires >
    UsageEvent -right-> EventType
}

note right of TM #BBDEFB
    **STEP 2 - Tracker receives the call.**
    "The Facade delegates to ScreenTimeTracker.
    It's a **Singleton** — one instance per device,
    otherwise sessions get double-counted."

    "onAppOpened() creates a new UsageSession.
    30 min later, user closes the app.
    onAppClosed() ends the session,
    computes duration, and fires a
    UsageEvent. But who receives it?"
    **Pattern: Singleton** | **(SRP)**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  DOMAIN MODELS (referenced by tracker)
' ====================================================================
package "Domain Models" as DM #E8F5E9 {

    class AppInfo {
        - packageName : String
        - displayName : String
        - category : AppCategory
        --
        + getPackageName() : String
        + getDisplayName() : String
    }

    enum AppCategory {
        SOCIAL_MEDIA
        PRODUCTIVITY
        ENTERTAINMENT
        GAMING
        OTHER
    }

    class UsageSession {
        - sessionId : String
        - app : AppInfo
        - startTime : long
        - endTime : long
        --
        + getDurationMillis() : long
        + isActive() : boolean
        + endSession(endTime) : void
    }

    class DailyUsageSummary {
        - date : LocalDate
        - app : AppInfo
        - totalTimeMillis : long
        - sessionCount : int
        - sessions : List
        --
        + getTotalMinutes() : int
        + addSession(session) : void
    }

    AppInfo -right-> AppCategory
    UsageSession --> AppInfo : for app >
    DailyUsageSummary --> AppInfo : per app >
    DailyUsageSummary o-- UsageSession : aggregates >
}

note left of DM #C8E6C9
    "These are the core data models.
    **AppInfo** = which app (Instagram).
    **UsageSession** = one 30-min window.
    **DailyUsageSummary** = all sessions
    of one app rolled up for one day.
    Pure data, no logic. **(SRP)**"
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: OBSERVERS — Observer Pattern
' ====================================================================
package "Observers" as OM #FFF3E0 {

    interface UsageEventObserver <<Observer>> {
        + onUsageEvent(event) : void
    }

    class PersistenceObserver <<ConcreteObserver>> {
        - repository : UsageRepository
        --
        + onUsageEvent(event) : void
    }

    class StatisticsUpdateObserver <<ConcreteObserver>> {
        - statsService : UsageStatisticsService
        --
        + onUsageEvent(event) : void
    }

    class UsageLimitObserver <<ConcreteObserver>> {
        - dailyLimits : Map
        - currentUsage : Map
        --
        + onUsageEvent(event) : void
        + setDailyLimit(app, minutes) : void
        - checkLimit(app) : void
    }

    UsageEventObserver <|.. PersistenceObserver
    UsageEventObserver <|.. StatisticsUpdateObserver
    UsageEventObserver <|.. UsageLimitObserver
}

note right of OM #FFE0B2
    **STEP 3 - Event fans out to observers.**
    "The tracker doesn't save data or update UI
    itself. That would be tight coupling.
    Instead it calls notifyObservers()."

    "Three observers react independently:
    1. **PersistenceObserver** -> saves to disk
    2. **StatisticsObserver** -> refreshes UI
    3. **LimitObserver** -> checks daily cap"

    "Want SMS alerts later? Add 1 observer.
    Tracker code never changes."
    **Pattern: Observer** | **(OCP, SRP)**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: PERSISTENCE — Repository + Strategy
' ====================================================================
package "Persistence" as PM #FFEBEE {

    interface UsageRepository <<Repository>> {
        + saveSession(session) : void
        + getSessions(app, date) : List
        + getDailySummary(app, date) : DailyUsageSummary
        + getAllSummaries(start, end) : List
        + deleteOlderThan(date) : void
    }

    class UsageRepositoryImpl {
        - strategy : PersistenceStrategy
        - retentionDays : int
        --
        + saveSession(session) : void
        + getSessions(app, date) : List
        + getDailySummary(app, date) : DailyUsageSummary
        + getAllSummaries(start, end) : List
        + deleteOlderThan(date) : void
    }

    interface PersistenceStrategy <<Strategy>> {
        + write(key, data) : void
        + read(key) : String
        + delete(key) : void
        + readRange(prefix, start, end) : List
    }

    class FilePersistenceStrategy <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
        - baseDirectory : String
    }

    class SQLitePersistenceStrategy <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
        - databasePath : String
    }

    class SharedPrefsPersistenceStrategy <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
        - prefsName : String
    }

    UsageRepository <|.. UsageRepositoryImpl
    UsageRepositoryImpl -right-> PersistenceStrategy : delegates >
    PersistenceStrategy <|.. FilePersistenceStrategy
    PersistenceStrategy <|.. SQLitePersistenceStrategy
    PersistenceStrategy <|.. SharedPrefsPersistenceStrategy
}

note right of PM #FFCDD2
    **STEP 4 - Data hits the persistence layer.**
    "PersistenceObserver calls saveSession().
    But it doesn't call SQLite directly."

    "**Repository Pattern** — business logic
    calls UsageRepository interface. It never
    knows if it's SQLite, file, or cloud. **(DIP)**"

    "**Strategy Pattern** — the actual storage
    is pluggable. SQLite for prod,
    InMemory for unit tests.
    New backend = 1 new class. **(OCP, LSP)**"

    "This is how data survives reboots."
    **Patterns: Repository + Strategy**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: STATISTICS — Builder
' ====================================================================
package "Statistics" as SM #F3E5F5 {

    class UsageStatisticsService <<Service>> {
        - repository : UsageRepository
        --
        + getTodayUsage(app) : DailyUsageSummary
        + getWeeklyReport() : UsageReport
        + getMostUsedApps(days) : List
        + getAverageDaily(app) : int
    }

    class UsageReportBuilder <<Builder>> {
        - startDate : LocalDate
        - endDate : LocalDate
        - summaries : List
        --
        + setDateRange(start, end) : UsageReportBuilder
        + addDailySummary(s) : UsageReportBuilder
        + build() : UsageReport
    }

    class UsageReport {
        - startDate : LocalDate
        - endDate : LocalDate
        - totalScreenTimeMillis : long
        - appBreakdown : Map
        --
        + getTotalHours() : double
        + getDailyAverage() : double
        + getAppBreakdown() : Map
    }

    UsageStatisticsService -right-> UsageReportBuilder : uses >
    UsageReportBuilder -right-> UsageReport : builds >
}

note right of SM #E1BEE7
    **STEP 5 - User checks screen time.**
    "Later, the user opens the app to see
    'how much time did I spend today?'
    StatisticsService reads from repository
    and builds a UsageReport."

    "Report has 5+ fields. Instead of a
    monster constructor, we use
    **Builder Pattern**: setDateRange()
    .addDailySummary().build()"
    **Pattern: Builder** | **(SRP)**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: RETENTION — 7-day cleanup
' ====================================================================
package "Retention" as RM #E0F7FA {

    class DataRetentionManager <<Service>> {
        - repository : UsageRepository
        - retentionDays : int = 7
        --
        + purgeExpiredData() : void
        + getRetentionWindow() : DateRange
        + isWithinRetention(date) : boolean
    }

    class DateRange {
        - startDate : LocalDate
        - endDate : LocalDate
        --
        + contains(date) : boolean
        + getDayCount() : int
    }

    DataRetentionManager -right-> DateRange : uses >
}

note right of RM #B2EBF2
    **STEP 6 - Cleanup.**
    "On every app startup, this manager calls
    repo.deleteOlderThan(today - 7).
    Keeps only last 7 days. Storage bounded.
    Change to 30 days? One field." **(SRP)**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **STEP 7 - Wrap up.**
    "To summarize, we traced one user action through the system:
    **Facade** received it, **Singleton tracker** created a session,
    **Observer** fanned out to 3 independent reactions,
    **Repository + Strategy** persisted data durably,
    **Builder** constructed the stats report,
    and **Retention** enforces the 7-day window.
    6 patterns, each solving a specific problem."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  CROSS-MODULE RELATIONSHIPS
' ====================================================================
DigitalWellbeingSystem -down-> ScreenTimeTracker
DigitalWellbeingSystem -down-> UsageStatisticsService
DigitalWellbeingSystem -down-> DataRetentionManager

ScreenTimeTracker --> UsageSession : creates >
ScreenTimeTracker -down-> UsageEventObserver : notifies >

PersistenceObserver -down-> UsageRepository : saves via >
StatisticsUpdateObserver -down-> UsageStatisticsService : refreshes >
UsageStatisticsService -down-> UsageRepository : reads from >
DataRetentionManager -down-> UsageRepository : cleans >


